anyhow /ˈɛnɪˌhaʊ/

1. ADV Anyhow means the same as . 反正 (同)(anyway) 

2. ADV If you do something anyhow , you do it in a careless or untidy way. 马虎随便地 [ADV after v] 

例： Her discarded books were piled up just anyhow. 她丢弃的书被胡乱地堆了起来。

